HEADWORD: Chopfallen
<hw>Chop`fall`en</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Having the lower
chop or jaw depressed; hence, crestfallen; dejected; dispirited;
downcast. See <er>Chapfallen</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

